                   "message":  "PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-DOC-RECONCILE: record dynamic Play enablement (#302), docs-only\n\nForward-only planning-substrate hygiene after #302 (9960b30,\nPLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-ENABLE) made the Play menu items dynamically enabled (grey out\nper live PlayState). Prepends a new 2026-06-03 snapshot to Status.md + HANDOFF.md,\ninserts a new \"2026-06-03 - Play-menu items now dynamically enabled per live\nPlayState (#302)\" subsection into plans/BASELINE.md above the A4 subsection, and\nappends a matching change.md entry. All A4/A3/A2/A1 snapshots, subsections, and\nentries are byte-identical (pure prepend/insert/append, +30/-0).\n\nRecords: PlayState::can_* (pinned to the real transitions) -\u003e MenuStateSnapshot\n(new editor-state observation aggregator) -\u003e MenuStateHandoff (3rd snapshot\nhandoff) -\u003e host add_enabled. Narrows the A4 \"dynamic predicates / per-frame\nre-resolve (no toggle labels yet)\" deferred line.\n\nPrecise (no over-claim): this is a BESPOKE per-frame enablement channel, NOT the\nW08 registry Predicate/resolve path (still deferred), nor dynamic labels /\naccelerator display / plugin entries / File-Edit-View enablement.\n\nDocs-only: no Rust / Cargo / rustdoc / lint-doc change (the #302 rustdoc already\ndescribes the feature; its 4 stale-prose rounds widened the handoff/snapshot\nlistings). Gate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
